    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PBCH resource element allocation in ALAMOUTI mode\n\n### Summary\nThe `allocate_pbch_REs_in_RB()` function in `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/pbch.c` was not correctly handling resource element allocation when using ALAMOUTI MIMO mode. This caused incorrect PBCH transmission and potential memory access issues.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/pbch.c`: Fixed assignment operators and added boundary checks in ALAMOUTI processing\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running OAI eNB with 2 antenna ports configured for PBCH transmission, the eNB may crash with segmentation fault or produce incorrect PBCH symbols. Users observed that UEs were unable to properly decode the PBCH, leading to RRC connection failures during initial access.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure eNB with 2 antenna ports\n2. Enable ALAMOUTI transmission mode\n3. Attempt UE attachment\n4. Observe RRC connection failures or eNB crash\n\nThe issue is most noticeable in environments with high pilot symbol density where the ALAMOUTI precoding logic incorrectly increments resource element indices beyond the resource block boundaries.\n"
}